Nyali MP hopeful Simon Adalla has urged legislators to transform bursaries into long-term scholarship to supplement Higher Education Loans Board cash.He urged President Uhuru Kenyatta to end runaway graft to ensure this is realised by saving billions of shillings. &ldquo;Education is one of the pillars of our country and shouldn&rsquo;t be taken for granted,&rdquo; he told the Star on Friday.